                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>No business will be transacted or interviews had on the Jewish Sabbath&#44; from one hour before sunset<lb/> on Friday&#44; until one hour after sunset on Saturday&#44; or on the Jewish Festivals&#44;<lb/> and no letters will be opened on those days.<lb/></p>
            <p>Jerusalem &#40;Holy City&#41; the glory of all lands.							&#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>ALFRED A. MARCUS &#38; SON&#44;<lb/>
                &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/>
                Alfred A. Marcus.		Simeon Marcus.<lb/>
                DIAMOND MERCHANTS AND IMPORTERS.<lb/>
                PURCHASER&#39;S OF REAL ESTATE &#40;LANDED PROPERTY&#41;<lb/>
                A Large Stock of Diamonds&#44; Rough and Polished&#44; also Precious Stones in every Variety always on Hand.<lb/>
                103 STATE STREET.<lb/></p>
            <p>Residence&#44;<lb/>
                127 Dartmouth Street&#44; Hard by the Bridge.<lb/>
                Telephone&#44; Tremont 457.<lb/></p>
            <p>Boston&#44; Ellul 12 A. M. 5656<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi> Dr. S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>My very dear Doctor<lb/></p>
            <p>We were very sorry to hear<lb/> that you were unwell but we pray<lb/> to Heaven that you are again all<lb/> <sic>recovrd</sic> &#38; that your life may be<lb/> spared for its usefulness for a<lb/> great many years to come<lb/></p>
            <p>We are sending you an Album of<lb/> Flowers from the Holy City for your<lb/> kind acceptance<lb/></p>
            <p>On Tuesday Ellul 16 is the 44th year<lb/> since my dearest Father &#91;&#63;&#93; died we<lb/> send &#36;5. for you to donate to any charity your<lb/> heart desires<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Wishing you &#38; all dear to you<lb/> to compliments of the coming<lb/> New Year &#38; that it may bring to us<lb/> all one of uninterrupted happiness<lb/> &#38; Joy<lb/> Remain<lb/> Your&#39;s most faithfully<lb/> Alfred A. Marcus &#38; Son<lb/></p>
            </body>
